This comes follows a week after the department handed over a R50 million primary school in Bizana. CAPE TOWN - The Eastern Cape Department of Education has handed over a new R45 million high school to the Marhubeni community. This comes follows a week after the department handed over a R50 million primary school in Bizana. “We are honouring a promise that we made as the department that we will ensure that learners are taught in a conducive environment,” said spokesperson Malibongwe Mtima. Built at a cost of R45m. The school comes fully equipped with a multipurpose center, library, computer lab with internet connection, science lab, 24 toilets and 26 classrooms catering 992 learners #ASIDI @ElijahMhlanga pic.twitter.com/oaFejBWt4n 